⦁	Introduction where you discuss the business problem and who would be interested in this project.

⦁Tourism is a 8 trillion dollar industry in which some cities rely heavily upon for their revenues. 
Explore the top 2 tourist cities and the bottom 2 tourist cities(out of 100) to see how similar or dissimilar they are. 
Do the cities with more tourism have a higher concentration of a particular venue?


Target audience- City planners, entrepenuers.

Idea is to provide insight that cities can use to improve tourism. What do successful tourist cities have in common? 
If a city is looking to expand their tourism what sort of infrastructure to they need to establish? 
if an entrepenuer is looking to capitalize on tourism what sort of venue should they look to create?

